On the Assessable Unit, the "Minimum Required Frequency" will now be called "Minimum Required M&T Frequency". This frequency will be determined based on the Last Approved Residual Risk Rating instead of the inherent risk rating. The frequency will be annually for High, every 2 years for Medium, and every 3 years for Low.

Furthermore, on the Control Result for the Assessable Unit, the Next Control Test Year (System) will reflect the new changes to the "Minimum Required M&T Frequency". Additionally, a new field called "OE Assessment Type" will be available under the Additional Information section, sourced directly from ORMS.
